blockToken(address).notice: Block token from being bridged. A blocked token cannot be deployed. Note: Only an unserviced token can be blocked. In order to deactivate a serviced tokens see 'deactivateToken'.

deactivateToken(address).notice: Deactivates bridging of a specific token. A deactivated token is blocked for deposits and cannot be re-deployed. Note: Only serviced tokens can be deactivated. In order to block an unserviced tokens see 'blockToken'.

enrollTokenBridge(address).notice: Enrolls a token bridge for a specific token.

getRegistry().notice: Returns the address of the Starkgate Registry contract.
